page.title: 14JUBILEE ROAD, MALBOROUGH
page.content: We know that the houses in Jubilee Road vary in design between{Cornish {Units}and ordinary council houses.Down the bottom of Jubilee Road where a piece of land called Tung was, they built a housing estate. In Jubilee Road you have to turn around at the bottom because it is a cul_de_sac. In Jubilee Road the Cornish Unit houses were built in nineteen forty seven and the other council houses were built in nineteen fifty. Where Jubilee Road is,there was a field called {Jubilee Field.}Before all Jubilee Road was called Jubilee Road, some of it was called Collaton Way. In Jubilee Road there are twenty four council houses altogether.
